'''Ábelová''' (earlier also Abelová, Jabelová; {{lang-hu| Ábelfalva, before 1907 Abellehota, before 1873 Abelova}}) is a village and municipality in the [[Lučenec District]] in the [[Banská Bystrica Region]] of [[Slovakia]].

==History==
The village arose in the early 13th century. In [[history|historical records]], it was first mentioned in 1275 (''Abelfeuld''). It belonged to [[Halič]] and until the 16th century partly also to [[Divín]].
